A pleasant time spent in this museum. The exhibition on the absynte is very well done. We can see impressionist paintings around the theme of the absentee. And detailed explanations on the relationship that the painters had with the absentee. Van Gogh, Renoir, Manet, Picasso, Toulouse Lautrec and other painters.....

Small museum which traces the existence of a place where a musette ball was held on the banks of the Seine. This museum is run by a voluntary association. Open Wednesdays and Sundays in the afternoon. This museum hosts temporary exhibitions.

Small museum located next to the Ch√¢teau Chanorier, presents numerous objects relating to the old tavern and offers exhibitions on artists from the end of the 19th century. On the ground floor, there is the small museum of the Old Croissy Association (free), the volunteers will explain the history of the town, particularly the market gardening period. You can also enjoy the neighboring park or take a walk on the banks of the Seine below. The museum is located about a kilometer south of the Chatou-Croissy RER station.
